The City of Johannesburg is offering a R50 000 reward for any information that could lead to the arrest and prosecution of those who robbed its offices last week. A gang of ten suspects tied up a security guard at the City’s Midrand offices and stole computers and other goods valued at around R1 million. In a possibly related incident not far away – criminals later broke into the Rabie Ridge Library and made off with goods valued at R70 000. The City of Johannesburg’s Lucky Sindane, “About ten criminals overpowered our security personnel at the Region A offices, then the same incident happened at the Rabie Ridge Library. We are appealing to anyone with information to please come forward. They can contact 0800  002 587.” 